    "# Create the correlation heatmap in seaborn by applying a heatmap onto the correlation matrix and the subplots defined above.\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "635da8c1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Findings with more granularity with the added detail of coefficients show:\n",
    "###  A weak positive relationship between education and income mobility (+0.23), \n",
    "###  A weak positive relationship between education and urban dwellers (+0.22), \n",
    "###  A weak positive relationship between income mobility and urban dwellers (+0.16), \n",
    "###  A weak negative relationship between sex (being male) and being employed (-0.19), \n",
    "### A moderate positive relationship between education and having a financial bank account (+0.39), and moderate negative relationship between education and having a debit card (-0.40) *meaning educated respondees are more likely to have a bank account as well as have debit cards based on the the response coding in the surveys*.\n",
    "### A strong positive relationship that if you have an account it will be a financial/bank account (+0.89) vs. mobile money (+0.5).\n",
    "### A moderate positive relationship between regioncode and having a debit card (+0.39) (*should be negative based on response coding in the financial account survey*).\n",
    "### A moderate negative relationship between regioncode and having a financial account (-0.38).\n"
   ]
  },

    "sns.lmplot(x = 'income_quint', y = 'educ', data = df_corr)\n"
